Key Match Events: Marcus Semien hit a game-ending single into the left field corner to score Leody Taveras as the Texas Rangers rallied from a five-run deficit for a 6-5 win over the Seattle Mariners
Miscellaneous Highlights: The win kept the playoff-chasing Seattle Mariners from gaining ground in the AL wild card race
The game was played at Globe Life Field in Arlington, Texas, with an attendance of 39,882
Others: Bryan Woo pitched 6.0 innings with 7 hits, 4 earned runs, 1 walk, and 4 strikeouts for the Mariners
Andrew Heaney pitched 5.2 innings with 7 hits, 4 earned runs, 1 walk, and 4 strikeouts for the Rangers
